Risk Management Program
Executive Summary
Dawn Foods Products, Inc.
Frozen Division
1300 East Summit Street
Crown Point, Indiana

I.	Introduction
A Risk Management Program has been implemented at Dawn Food Products, Inc. ¿ Frozen Division (Dawn Foods) for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This Program summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. The Risk Management Plan (RMP) is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including: italic
·	Introduction;
·	Dawn Foods policies to protect health, environment, and safety;
·	Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;
·	Hazard Assessment;
·	Prevention Program;
·	Five-Year Accident History;
·	Emergency Response Plan; 
·	Emergency Communications;
·	Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures
·	Planned changes to improve safety; and
·	Management Program

II.	Dawn Food¿s Policies To Protect Health, Environment and Safety
Risk management and safety are important concerns at Dawn Foods; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. Dawn Foods is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment. It is Dawn Food¿s policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations.

